energy.usef.core.data.xml.bean.message

Class FlexOrder

  • java.lang.Object
    • energy.usef.core.data.xml.bean.message.FlexBase
      • energy.usef.core.data.xml.bean.message.FlexOrder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Message

    public class FlexOrder
extends FlexBase
implements Message
    FlexOrder messages are used by DSOs and BRPs to purchase flexibility from an Aggregator based on a previous FlexOffer. A FlexOrder message contains a list of PTUs, with, for each PTU, the change in consumption or production to be realized by the Aggregator, plus the accepted price to be paid by the DSO or BRP for this amount of flexibility. This PTU list should be copied from the FlexOffer message without modification: Aggregator implementations will (and must) reject FlexOrder messages where the PTU list is not exactly the same as offered.

         <attribute name="Currency" use="required" type="{}ISO4217Currency" />
         <attribute name="OrderReference" use="required" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" />
       </extension>
     </complexContent>
   </complexType>
